line_1: And country girls are oft unsound;
line_2: But vice is in the cottage sound,

line_1: And swore that long, though rotten and unsound,
line_2: On this the Liver writh'd himself around,

line_1: Till, in mid-green, she trusts a place unsound,
line_2: And deeply plunges in th' adhesive ground;

line_1: So two sear trees, dry, stunted, and unsound,
line_2: Each other catch, when dropping to the ground;

line_1: Weak is that throne, and in itself unsound
line_2: Which takes not solid virtue for its ground.

line_1: Of Limbs enormous, but withal unsound,
line_2: Unwieldy Man! with Belly monstrous round,

line_1: Till sapp'd their strength, and every part unsound,
line_2: Down, down they sink, and spread a ruin round.

line_1: Juries were pack'd, and Judges were unsound;
line_2: Thro' the whole kingdom not one PRATT was found.

line_1: Tis plain, this Lobe is so unsound,
line_2: S— prints, before the Months go round.
